1. Introduction: Describe the system requirements for an IT student portfolio website.
A single-main-page and some side pages personal website.
Display personal information, skills, projects, blogs and related documents.
Provide a professional platform to introduce yourself.
Allow uploading of CVs and other documents.
Integrate micro-interactions and animations for increased interactivity.
Display name, photo, brief information, main skills. -> link to CV page
List projects with description, photo, GitHub/demo link.
Filter by project type (web, app, research, etc.).
View details of each article (markdown or rich text).
Link to social networks (LinkedIn, GitHub, FB).
Angular: powerful but quite heavy for student portfolio, high learning curve.
Vue:a young framework, not as supported and popular as React and Angular
Spring Boot / Django: good but heavy backend, not suitable for just portfolio showcase.
Kubernetes: too advanced, difficult for students to deploy in practice if they are just starting out.
